{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}

{% block content %}

  {# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}
  {# HERO                                                       #}
  {# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}
  <section class="relative flex flex-col min-h-screen px-6 pb-12 mx-auto overflow-hidden md:px-14 pt-28"
           aria-labelledby="hero-heading">

    {# Ghost background m² #}
    <span class="hidden lg:block absolute right-[-0.04em] top-1/2 -translate-y-[48%]
                 font-display font-semibold italic select-none pointer-events-none
                 leading-none text-[20vw] text-transparent
                 h-enter-fade d-7"
          aria-hidden="true"
          style="-webkit-text-stroke: 1px #C9BCA9;">m²</span>

    {# Coordinate watermark #}
    <div class="hidden md:block absolute top-32 right-14
                font-code text-[0.58rem] tracking-wider
                text-[#C9BCA9] text-right leading-loose
                h-enter-fade d-7"
         aria-hidden="true">
      30.2672° N<br>97.7431° W<br>Austin, TX
    </div>

    {# Main hero content #}
    <div class="flex flex-col justify-center flex-1 max-w-6xl px-6 md:px-14">

      <p class="h-enter d-1 font-code text-[0.6rem] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#1C5B72] mb-7">
        Systems · Spaces · Things
      </p>

      <h1 id="hero-heading"
          class="h-enter d-2 font-display font-light italic leading-[1.05] text-[#1A1510] mb-8"
          style="font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 8vw, 6.2rem); letter-spacing: -0.015em;">
        The questions<br>
        are always<br>
        the same.
      </h1>

      <p class="h-enter d-3 font-display text-[#4A4035] mb-10"
         style="font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.2vw, 1.45rem); letter-spacing: 0.01em;">
        Where are things?
        <span class="mx-2 text-[#C9BCA9]">·</span>
        Where should they be?
        <span class="mx-2 text-[#C9BCA9]">·</span>
        What is the gap telling us?
      </p>

      <p class="h-enter d-4 font-code text-[0.65rem] tracking-widest text-[#7A6E65]">
        Melanie E. Magdalena
        <span class="mx-2 text-[#C9BCA9]">·</span>
        Austin, TX
      </p>

    </div>

  </section>

  <hr class="border-none h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-[#C9BCA9] to-transparent">


  {# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}
  {# THROUGHLINE                                                #}
  {# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}
  <section id="throughline"
           class="max-w-6xl px-6 py-24 mx-auto md:px-14 md:py-32"
           aria-labelledby="throughline-heading">

    <p class="s-label reveal font-code text-[0.58rem] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#1C5B72] mb-14">
      The throughline
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1.65fr] gap-14 lg:gap-28">

      {# Left: sticky label #}
      <div class="self-start reveal lg:sticky lg:top-28">
        <h2 id="throughline-heading"
            class="font-display font-light italic text-[#1A1510] leading-[1.1] mb-8"
            style="font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3.2vw, 2.6rem);">
          One way<br>of seeing.<br>Many places<br>to look.
        </h2>
        <ul class="font-code text-[0.62rem] tracking-wider text-[#7A6E65]
                   leading-loose list-none m-0 p-0" aria-label="Career arc">
          <li>Archaeology →</li>
          <li>Digital Systems →</li>
          <li>Security →</li>
          <li>Logistics</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      {# Right: narrative #}
      <div class="space-y-5 font-reading text-[1rem] leading-[1.85] text-[#4A4035]">

        <p class="reveal reveal-d1">
          At twenty, I published a spatial analysis of Maya settlements in Belize — mapping where people built, what moved between them, and what the gaps revealed about how a society organized itself around scarce resources.
        </p>

        <p class="reveal reveal-d2">
          I've been asking the same questions in every role since.
          <strong class="font-normal text-[#1A1510]">Where are things? Where should they be? What is the gap telling us?</strong>
        </p>

        <p class="reveal reveal-d3">
          As a digital systems architect for nonprofits and universities, I built data structures by asking what an organization actually needed to know about itself — not what it was already tracking. As a security officer, I redesigned patrol routes around what the floor plan didn't show. Now, I've trained in a regional food bank's warehouse distributing 63 million meals annually, learning how physical goods move from dock to table — and where the process breaks down.
        </p>

        <p class="reveal reveal-d4">The tools change. The questions don't.</p>

        {# Timeline tick marks #}
        <div class="relative pt-10 mt-6 reveal reveal-d4">
          <span class="absolute top-[1.4rem] left-0 right-0 h-px bg-[#C9BCA9]"
                aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <ol class="grid grid-cols-4 p-0 m-0 list-none">
            {% set timeline = [
              { year: "2012",    label: "Maya spatial\nanalysis\npublished, age 20" },
              { year: "2014–22", label: "Digital systems\narchitecture\nnonprofit & web" },
              { year: "2023–24", label: "Security\n& route design" },
              { year: "2024 →",  label: "Inventory, logistics\n& supply chain\nongoing" }
            ] %}
            {% for item in timeline %}
            <li class="relative pt-5 pr-2">
              <span class="absolute top-[-0.3rem] left-0 w-px h-3 bg-[#C9BCA9]"
                    aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <p class="font-code text-[0.58rem] tracking-wider text-[#1C5B72] mb-1">
                {{ item.year }}
              </p>
              <p class="font-code text-[0.56rem] tracking-wide text-[#7A6E65]
                        leading-relaxed whitespace-pre-line">
                {{ item.label }}
              </p>
            </li>
            {% endfor %}
          </ol>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="border-none h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-[#C9BCA9] to-transparent">

  {# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}
  {# THREE LENSES                                               #}
  {# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}
  <section class="bg-[#EDE5D4] px-6 md:px-14 py-24 md:py-32"
           aria-labelledby="lenses-heading">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="s-label reveal font-code text-[0.58rem] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#1C5B72] mb-14">
        How I work
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 divide-y md:divide-y-0 md:divide-x divide-[#C9BCA9]">

        {% set lenses = [
          {
            num:   "01",
            word:  "Systems",
            intro: "Build. Audit. Ask why.",
            body:  "I build them, document them, and ask why they were built this way in the first place. Not just: does it work — but what assumptions is this built on, and are those assumptions still true? Whether it's a data architecture for a nonprofit or a receiving workflow at a warehouse, the audit question is the same."
          },
          {
            num:   "02",
            word:  "Spaces",
            intro: "Physical. Digital. Both.",
            body:  "A warehouse floor is a spatial optimization problem. So is a nonprofit's information architecture. I move between them because the logic is the same at both scales: who needs to get to what, how fast, and what's in the way. The space changes. The method doesn't."
          },
          {
            num:   "03",
            word:  "Things",
            intro: "Count. Move. Recover.",
            body:  "Goods, data, people, ideas — things need to be tracked, moved, and found again when something goes wrong. Precision matters because it's how we know what's real versus what the system thinks is real. The distance between those two is where most operational problems actually live."
          }
        ] %}

        {% for lens in lenses %}
        <div class="reveal reveal-d{{ loop.index }} px-0 py-10 md:px-10 md:py-0 {% if not loop.first %}md:pl-10{% endif %}">
          <p class="font-code text-[0.58rem] tracking-[0.18em] text-[#C9BCA9] mb-4">
            {{ lens.num }}
          </p>
          <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-[#1C5B72] mb-1"
              style="font-size: 1.6rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
            {{ lens.word }}
          </h3>
          <p class="font-display italic text-[#4A4035] mb-5" style="font-size: 1.05rem;">
            {{ lens.intro }}
          </p>
          <p class="font-reading text-[0.93rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4A4035]">
            {{ lens.body }}
          </p>
        </div>
        {% endfor %}

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="border-none h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-[#C9BCA9] to-transparent">

  {# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}
  {# WORK                                                       #}
  {# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}
  <section class="max-w-6xl px-6 py-24 mx-auto md:px-14 md:py-32"
           aria-labelledby="work-heading">

    <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-14">
      <p class="s-label reveal font-code text-[0.58rem] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#1C5B72]">
        Selected work
      </p>
      <a href="/work/"
         class="font-code text-[0.6rem] tracking-[0.12em] uppercase text-[#7A6E65]
                hover:text-[#1C5B72] transition-colors border-b border-[#C9BCA9]
                hover:border-[#1C5B72]">
        All work →
      </a>
    </div>

    {# Work cards — SP-forward order:
       1. CHC (live, mission-driven, Lane 2 primary evidence)
       2. MIT Innovation One (complex multi-stakeholder systems)
       3. Maya paper (origin story, intellectual depth signal)
       4. Portfolio (analytical work)
    #}
    <div class="grid max-w-5xl grid-cols-1 gap-5 mx-auto md:grid-cols-2">

      {# ── Card 1: CHC ── #}
      <a href="https://hungercenter.org"
         target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
         class="work-card reveal reveal-d1
                group block bg-white border border-[#DDD4C4]
                p-8 no-underline"
         aria-label="Congressional Hunger Center — Digital Platform Redesign (opens hungercenter.org)">
        <p class="font-code text-[0.56rem] tracking-[0.16em] uppercase text-[#1C5B72] mb-5">
          Systems Implementation · UX · Nonprofit
        </p>
        <h3 class="font-display font-light italic text-[#1A1510] leading-tight mb-3"
            style="font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 2.5vw, 1.9rem);">
          Congressional Hunger Center
        </h3>
        <p class="font-reading text-[0.92rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#4A4035] mb-6">
          Full digital platform redesign for a DC-based policy leadership organization.
          40+ page information architecture, 13-template design system, structured
          content management for non-technical staff, interactive global partner map.
          <strong class="font-normal text-[#1A1510]">Staff can now update the site
          without a developer.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="font-code text-[0.6rem] tracking-wider text-[#7A6E65]
                  group-hover:text-[#1C5B72] transition-colors">
          hungercenter.org ↗
        </p>
      </a>

      {# ── Card 2: MIT ── #}
      <div class="work-card reveal reveal-d2
                  bg-[#EDE5D4] border border-[#DDD4C4] p-8">
        <p class="font-code text-[0.56rem] tracking-[0.16em] uppercase text-[#1C5B72] mb-5">
          Systems Architecture · Data · Education
        </p>
        <h3 class="font-display font-light italic text-[#1A1510] leading-tight mb-3"
            style="font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 2.5vw, 1.9rem);">
          MIT Innovation Initiative
        </h3>
        <p class="font-reading text-[0.92rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#4A4035] mb-6">
          Three-role student placement platform for MIT's Office of the Provost.
          Federated Airtable data backbone, custom bidirectional sync plugin,
          MIT Kerberos SSO. Built to track student innovation pathways across a
          fragmented ecosystem of labs, programs, and ventures.
          <strong class="font-normal text-[#1A1510]">Operational infrastructure
          the institution had never had.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="font-code text-[0.6rem] tracking-wider text-[#C9BCA9]">
          Case study coming soon
        </p>
      </div>

      {# ── Card 3: Maya Paper ── #}
      <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1M_AnkZwVMGHtMyWK8DppgLErJVlz-nhD/view"
         class="work-card reveal reveal-d3
                group block bg-[#1C5B72] border border-[#1C5B72]
                p-8 no-underline"
         aria-label="The Maya of Belize — spatial analysis, published 2012">
        <p class="font-code text-[0.56rem] tracking-[0.16em] uppercase text-[#D4E8EF]/70 mb-5">
          Spatial Analysis · Archaeology · 2012
        </p>
        <h3 class="mb-3 italic font-light leading-tight text-white font-display"
            style="font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 2.5vw, 1.9rem);">
          The Maya of Belize
        </h3>
        <p class="font-reading text-[0.92rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#D4E8EF] mb-6">
          Published at twenty. Spatial analysis of Maya settlement patterns — mapping
          where people built, what resources moved between nodes, and what the gaps
          revealed about societal organization. The origin of the question that runs
          through everything else here.
        </p>
        <p class="font-code text-[0.6rem] tracking-wider text-[#D4E8EF]/70
                  group-hover:text-white transition-colors">
          Read the paper →
        </p>
      </a>

      {# ── Card 4: Portfolio / Analytical work ── #}
      <a href="/work/"
         class="work-card reveal reveal-d4
                  border border-dashed border-[#C9BCA9] p-8">
        <p class="font-code text-[0.56rem] tracking-[0.16em] uppercase text-[#1C5B72] mb-5">
          Inventory · Data · Operations Analytics
        </p>
        <h3 class="font-display font-light italic text-[#1A1510] leading-tight mb-3"
            style="font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 2.5vw, 1.9rem);">
          Systems Portfolio
        </h3>
        <p class="font-reading text-[0.92rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#4A4035] mb-6">
          Eight analytical projects applying institutional theory to physical operations:
          ABC inventory segmentation, safety stock modeling, vendor scorecards,
          demand forecasting, and public asset audit simulation. Each one asks:
          what does the system assume it can know?
        </p>
        <p class="font-code text-[0.6rem] tracking-wider text-[#C9BCA9]">
          In progress — publishing through Spring 2026
        </p>
      </a>

    </div>
  </section>

{% endblock %}
